        "thermal_resistance": "R_tile_to_coolant should be sized so that at TDP with max coolant flow, T_die reaches ~65-70°C above T_coolant_in. Formula: R_tile = (T_target - T_coolant) * n_tiles / P_total. For H100 at 700W targeting 70°C with 40°C coolant: R = (70-40)*16/700 ≈ 0.7 K/W per tile.",
